<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-08-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-08-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="263" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d263">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Neill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Lima, Peru</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-08-03"><hi rend="italic">August 3, 1892</hi></date>.
                                (Received August 31.)</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 411.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my No. 407, of July 27, 1892,
                            in relation to the claim of the Hydrographic Commission of the Amazon, I
                            have the honor to transmit for your information a reply to my note
                            (accompanied with a translation) from the Peruvian foreign office.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard R. Neill.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                        <frus:attachment>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No. 411.]</seg></opener>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Señor <persName type="from">Larrabrue</persName>
                                    to Mr. <persName type="to">Neill</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign Office of Peru</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-08-02"><hi rend="italic">August 2, 1892</hi>.</date></dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 28.]</seg></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Chargé d’Affaires</hi>: I have again
                                forwarded to the marine and treasury offices the contents of your
                                esteemed note of the 27th ultimo, to which I have the honor to
                                reply, and I have strongly asked for a reply regarding the matter
                                you mention of the Hydrographic Commission of the Amazon claim, to
                                which end I have repeated the contents of the official notes
                                directed by this office to the said departments on the 20th of
                                August and the 2d of October, 1891, and the 5th of April of the
                                present year.</p>
                            <p>I hope soon to receive the information repeatedly asked for, in order
                                to enable me to give you an answer.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">E. Larrabrue y Unanne.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </frus:attachment>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>